      • createResource

        @Nullable
public Resource createResource(@Nonnull
                                          URI uri)
        Creates a resource with the given URI and returns it.

        Clients will typically not call this directly themselves; it's called by the resource set to create a resource.

        The uri must be registered in the PersistenceBackendFactoryRegistry.

        Specified by:
        createResource in interface Resource.Factory
        Parameters:
        uri - the URI.
        Returns:
        a new resource.
